svg.title: KEVIN-PFUNDER-MOBILE

text.tspan: Gayle graduated from Brigham Young University College of nursing in 1983.
She has had a wide range of nursing experiences including; Med/Surg,
Telemetry, Mom and baby nursing units.Gayle spent 16 years in the home
health field on nursing with the last 5 years as Director of Nursing at a very
busy Home Health Company.She then returned to the hospital setting for
the next 10 years in the Quality/Case Management area with 3 years as Case
Management Director.Gayle has now been at Dixie Technical College for a
year and half in the medical department, with the last 6 months as the
Director of Medical Programs at Dixie Technical College.

svg.text: Matt was raised and attended school in Enterprise, Utah. He spent
ten years working in the retail distribution industry. His passion for
CAD design and 3D printing led him to the Dixie Technical College
Drafting Program. Upon earning his certificate, he worked for
several local firms and businesses. Dixie Technical College is thrilled
to have Matt teaching MEchanical Drafting, using his passion and
knowledge to help students become successful CAD drafters.
